<div class="hero unit msides extratop2">
<p style="font-weight: bold;"> SF the hot bed of urban planning filmmaking? </p>

<p> Who knew San Francisco is a hotbed of urban planning inspired filmmaking? The SF Urban Film Fest will feature three days of locally produced documentaries and works-in-progress including Q&A with the filmmakers, Jeremy Ambers of Impossible Light, Ron Blatman of Saving the City, and Dan Goldes and Robert Cortland of 5 Blocks.  Each filmmaker approaches the topic of city-making differently, lyrically like Impossible Light, in contrasts as in Saving the City, and from the ground up as in 5 Blocks.  San Francisco is also the home of the Bay Area Video Coalition (BAVC), a non-profit turning on residents of all ages to storytelling and video production. Learn about BAVC at their booth on Sunday.</p>

</div>


